</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB636D2096BFFA12AD65093FADEF9FE" blockId="9.[151,1437,1338,1654]" pageId="9" pageNumber="510">
Comments: Species successfully introduced from 
<collectingCountry id="F31E7642096BFFA129155093FCE2FA6D" box="[772,875,1483,1509]" name="Australia" pageId="9" pageNumber="510">Australia</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry id="F31E7642096BFFA129825093FC40FA6D" box="[915,969,1483,1509]" name="United States of America" pageId="9" pageNumber="510">USA</collectingCountry>
in 1888 to control 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D51096BFFA12EBC5093FAD6FA6D" box="[1197,1375,1483,1509]" class="Insecta" family="Margarodidae" genus="Icerya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="510" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="purchasi">
<emphasis id="B97DEAC0096BFFA12EBC5093FAD6FA6D" box="[1197,1375,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="510">Icerya purchasi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C094D51096BFFA12F605093FED8F981" class="Insecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="510" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Hemiptera</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D51096BFFA12B4D50B7FD98F982" box="[348,529,1519,1546]" class="Insecta" family="Monophlebidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="510" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Monophlebidae</taxonomicName>
), a pest which was attacking the citrus plantations in 
<collectingRegion id="49CDF830096BFFA12E7750B7FB52F981" box="[1126,1243,1519,1545]" country="United States of America" name="California" pageId="9" pageNumber="510">California</collectingRegion>
. This species has been historically assigned to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D51096BFFA128BB534BFCE1F9A5" authority="Mulsant" authorityName="Mulsant" authorityYear="1850" box="[682,872,1555,1581]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Rodolia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="510" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DEAC0096BFFA128BB534BFC8AF9A5" box="[682,771,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="510">Rodolia</emphasis>
Mulsant
</taxonomicName>
, and has recently been assigned to 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D51096BFFA12EFD534BFA15F9A5" authority="Mulsant" authorityName="Mulsant" box="[1260,1436,1555,1581]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Novius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="510" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DEAC0096BFFA12EFD534BFAB3F9A4" box="[1260,1338,1555,1580]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="510">Novius</emphasis>
Mulsant
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF984B23096BFFA12AEE536FFD93F9D9" author="Kondo, T. &amp; Gonzalez, G." box="[255,538,1591,1617]" pageId="9" pageNumber="510" pagination="3" refId="ref16560" refString="Kondo, T. &amp; Gonzalez, G. (2020) Nomenclator entomologicus. No. 105. Newsletter. Sociedade Entomologica do Brasil, 53 (1), 3." type="journal article" year="2020">Kondo &amp; González 2020</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF984B23096BFFA12834536FFD55F9D9" author="Pang, H. &amp; Tang, X. F. &amp; Booth, R. G. &amp; Vandenberg, N. &amp; Forrester, J. &amp; Mchugh, J. &amp; Slipinski, A." box="[549,732,1591,1617]" pageId="9" pageNumber="510" pagination="1 - 24" refId="ref17416" refString="Pang, H., Tang, X. F., Booth, R. G., Vandenberg, N., Forrester, J., Mchugh, J. &amp; Slipinski, A. (2020) Revision of the Australian Coccinellidae (Coleoptera). Genus Novius Mulsant of Tribe Noviini. Annales Zoologici, 70, 1 - 24. https: // doi. org / 10.3161 / 00034541 ANZ 2020.70.1.001" type="journal article" year="2020">Pang et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
). Currently present in all South America, in 
<collectingCountry id="F31E7642096BFFA12ED4536FFA8BF9D9" box="[1221,1282,1591,1617]" name="Chile" pageId="9" pageNumber="510">Chile</collectingCountry>
introduced in 1931 (
<bibRefCitation id="EF984B23096BFFA12B2F5303FE58F9FD" author="Zuniga, E." box="[318,465,1626,1653]" pageId="9" pageNumber="510" pagination="175 - 183" refId="ref18886" refString="Zuniga, E. (1985) 80 anos de control biologico en Chile. Revision historica y evaluacion de proyectos desarrollados (1903 - 1983). Agricultura Tecnica, 45, 175 - 183." type="journal article" year="1985">Zúñiga 1985</bibRefCitation>
), with established populations between Arica and San Antonio (González 2006).
</paragraph>
